1. To use Postgres locally, Download PostgreSQL installer for Windows and then install it.
Installed :- postgresql-18.3-3-windows-x64
Username:- postgres
Password:- postgres
Port:- 5432

2. Add the bin location of this installed Postgres in environment variables
Now you can access the psql server from command line itself. If u want u can also download pgadmin or dbeaver
to query and view tables

To access from CLI:-
a. psql -U postgres
b. Enter password
c. Create new database:- CREATE DATABASE nexaroPayDB
d. To change current database :- \c nexaroPayDB
e. Now query using normal SQL

3. Install WSL for windows in order to install and use redis-cli.
a. Install wsl using :- wsl --install -d Ubuntu
b. Once installation is complete, ubuntu terminal will start and then you can use the terminal as normal linux.
c. Upgrade Ubuntu:- sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
d. Install JAVA 21:- sudo apt install -y openjdk-21-jdk
e. Install basic backend requirements:- sudo apt install -y build-essential curl wget git unzip
f. Set default wsl to Ubuntu:-  wsl --set-default Ubuntu
g. Install redis-server :- sudo apt-get install redis-server
h. Connect to redis-cli:- redis-cli
Redis Server:Port :- 127.0.0.1:6379
i. Check the Keys using:- keys *


4. Install Apache Kafka server for windows to start and use kafka.
a. I am Using Version:- kafka_2.13-4.0.2

Do the following steps if you are running kafka for the first time or if u have deleted the logs folder:-
i) Run this to generate $KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID :-  .\bin\windows\kafka-storage.bat random-uuid
ii) Format Log Directories :- .\bin\windows\kafka-storage.bat format --standalone -t $KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID -c .\config\server.properties

b. Run kafka server using :- .\bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat .\config\server.properties
c. To see what is being pushed in kafka run this command in new tab:-
.\windows\kafka-console-consumer.bat --topic USER-REGISTERED --bootstrap-server 0.0.0.0:9092,0.0.0.0:9093 --from-beginning

The name of the topic is defined in application.properties

